    "desc": "The world's most visited unofficial James Bond 007 website with daily updates, news & analysis of all things 007 and an extensive encyclopaedia. Get your dose of Ian Fleming's spy from Sean Connery to Daniel Craig with our expert online coverage and a rich, colour print magazine dedicated to spies.",
    "text": "x\nWELCOME TO MI6 HEADQUARTERS\nThis is the world's most visited unofficial James Bond 007 website with daily updates, news & analysis of all things 007 and an extensive encyclopaedia. Tap into Ian Fleming's spy from Sean Connery to Daniel Craig with our expert online coverage and a rich, colour print magazine dedicated to spies.\nLearn More About MI6 & James Bond →\nMI6\nThe Home of James Bond 007\nLatest\nFeatures\nEncyclopaedia\nMovies\nNo Time To Die (2021)\nPodcast\nComics\nLiterary\nGaming\nInteract\nLATEST FEATURES\nEXPANDED SCORE\nLaLaLand Records have a new Tomorrow Never Dies release\nRead More →\nFEATURED MAGAZINE\nRare, individually numbered and signed\nDB5 Lithograph\nNow available again in limited numbers\nWin Double Or Nothing\nCompetitions Enter for your chance to win copies of Kim Sherwood's new novel\n0147: Unmade Bond 24\nPodcast What ideas were jettisoned from the script that ultimately became Spectre?\nLaunch Event\nEvents Daniel Craig launched the new Omega Seamaster watches in London\n60th Seamasters\nCollecting Omega has launched two new watches to celebrate the anniversary\nEarlier Features\nMI6 Confidential Issue #66\nNo Going Back\nBuddy Movie\nLife After Bond\nCavill's Confirmation\nJohn Barry Plays 007\nThe Art of Film\n0146: Happy Anniversary Mr. Bond\nFor Your Eyes Only\nRe-Release Performance\nFeature Archive →\n\nGaming Oldest standing 'GoldenEye 007' speed run record finally broken...\nCollecting 'No Time To Die' 4K Ultra HD Blu-Ray set on sale for $9.99...\nBond News  Bond writer Paul Haggis ordered to pay $7.5m in legal case...\nBond News Bautista said Craig was not happy on 'SPECTRE' shoot...\nCollecting Daniel Craig 4K Blu-Ray boxset on sale in USA...\nBond News Ed Sheeran had started writing Bond 25 title song...\nMedia Alert 'Sound of 007' concert posted on YouTube...\nActor News  Timothy Dalton filming 'Yellowstone' prequel for Paramount+...\nActor News David Tennant discovers he was on 007 long list twenty years ago...\nEvent Bond concerts at the Royal Albert Hall in November...\nConnect with MI6\nSEARCH MI6\nCopyright mi6-hq.com, the Home of James Bond 007 © 2022\nSite Map • Contact • Press • Copyright Notice • Privacy Policy",
